# Ping targets configuration
# Format: host  [label]  t1  t2  t3
#   label: optional single token shown in waybar before the ms value
#          must be specified together with thresholds (no shell metacharacters)
#   t1: ms upper bound for "good"    (< t1)
#   t2: ms upper bound for "medium"  (< t2)
#   t3: ms upper bound for "bad"     (< t3); >= t3 = critical
#
# host can be a plain IP/hostname OR a shell command that resolves to one.
# Shell commands are detected by spaces, pipes, $, etc. and are evaluated.
#
# Targets are referenced positionally in config.jsonc:
#   %1 = first uncommented line, %2 = second, etc.
#
# Example:
#   "exec": "ping_status.sh '󰒍 %1 ISP: %2 GW: %3'"

8.8.8.8                                                         40  100  200
ip route | awk '/default/ {print $3; exit}'                 󰀂    2    5    10
192.168.0.104                                                   2    5    10
